{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The feature pyramid is a classic approach in object detection, and it can exploit multiscale feature information.",
    "In previous research, many object detection models that directly use image features extracted by the backbone network were proposed.",
    "However, to enable the complementary and fusion of features at different scales, thereby improving the performance of object detection and segmentation, the concept of a feature pyramid was introduced.",
    "Methods such as FPN 24, PANet 25, two-way FPN 26, etc.",
    "enhance model performance by fusing features of different scales through top-down or bottom-up pathways."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Methods such as FPN 24, PANet 25, two-way FPN 26, etc."
  ]
}